Looking at the code, the `sendDataResult` variable is created but only some of its members are initialized before being returned. The members `wantIo`, `fd`, `writeBuffLen`, `callbacks`, and `buffer` are never set.

The fix is to initialize these members before returning `sendDataResult`. Looking at the code, I can see that `connection->writeBuffLen` and `connection->buffer` are set, so we should also set these on `sendDataResult`.
```diff
--- a/library/src/main/cpp/napi/http2_common.h
+++ b/library/src/main/cpp/napi/http2_common.h
@@ -382,6 +382,11 @@ Connection SendData(Connection *connection, void *bufferData, int buffLen, str
     sendDataResult.dataFlags = dataFlags;
     sendDataResult.recvLargeDataFlags = recvLargeDataFlags;
     sendDataResult.streamId = streamId;
+    sendDataResult.wantIo = false;
+    sendDataResult.fd = -1;
+    sendDataResult.writeBuffLen = buffLen;
+    sendDataResult.callbacks = nullptr;
+    sendDataResult.buffer = static_cast<uint8_t *>(bufferData);
     return sendDataResult;
 }
```

